## Bundle layout

```
%%SKILL_NAME%%/
├── SKILL.md            # how to run this action
├── REFERENCE.md        # this file
├── SECURITY.md         # credential warning + sharing rules
├── data/
│   ├── session.har     # embedded session (live cookies/headers/bodies)
│   ├── flow.json       # ordered replay steps (indexes into session.har)
│   ├── lesson.json     # redacted distillation of the recording
│   ├── actions.js      # recorded UI steps (if the session had a UI flow)
│   └── meta.json       # lesson name, source URL, host, timestamp
└── scripts/
    ├── replay_api.py       # replay the API flow with substituted knobs
    ├── har_auth.py         # extract session cookies from the embedded HAR
    ├── replay_ui.sh        # UI replay -> mp4 proof (optional)
    ├── run_variant.js      # Playwright runner (skill-local profile)
    ├── variant.js          # editable UI scaffold (recorded steps)
    └── package.json        # playwright dependency
```

Everything resolves via the skill directory — no reference to `~/.web-lessons`
or the `generate-web-skills` skill.

Skills generated `--with-setup` also ship `scripts/setup.sh` +
`scripts/setup_login.js` and `data/auth_accounts.json`; each user's captured
login lands in `data/user-auth.<host>.har` (gitignored, never committed).

